Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.08,0:00:05.07,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,So he's drifting like that on purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.07,0:00:10.93,Italics,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Is he seriously trying to rally \Nhis way through the death zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.42,0:00:12.99,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Would you look at that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.26,0:00:18.41,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The attention flag the 86 lost on \Nentering the death zone has returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.77,0:00:23.75,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely Fujiwara Takumi's\N zero-counter steer drift.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.17,0:00:29.33,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if Project D's invincible downhill ace\N has appeared on the Ashinoko course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.05,0:00:35.76,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that people have been raving about \Nthe lunatic who drifted through every turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.33,0:00:40.00,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,But against suspension crafted \Nby the gifted test drivers at Porsche,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:42.00,Italics,Beckenbauer,0000,0000,0000,,his efforts will amount to nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.97,0:00:45.28,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And now, the Relay Straight!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.28,0:00:53.27,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a 2.5-liter engine, but the 7-speed PDK\Npowertrain gives it a remarkable top speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.80,0:00:59.45,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It was never in doubt! This German-made\N cyborg has proven his mettle!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.00,0:01:03.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Michael Beckenbauer \Ntakes pole with authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.01,0:01:08.46,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,But Sawatari Koki in second had previously\N set a fantastic new course record!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.70,0:01:14.01,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And amid this clash of the titans is \NKatagiri Kanata, who secured tenth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.01,0:01:16.84,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fsp4\fay-0.046\fs13\c&H878382&\pos(546.667,222.667)}Kamakura Station
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.52,0:01:20.16,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,This new class of "speed stars" is \Nlooking to upset the hierarchy in MFG!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.16,0:01:24.99,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Things are bubbling up nicely\Nheading into the Lake Ashinoko GT race!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.57,0:01:36.11,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,And Wakana was just being {\i1}so{\i0} yabai.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.11,0:01:40.95,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Sorry. {\fnTrebuchet MS}I still don't quite get \Nwhen it's appropriate to use "yabai."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:42.33,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.57,0:01:47.44,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, let's see... You can use it to describe\N some really good music, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.44,0:01:52.34,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Or when the food at a place you've never \Nbeen to is so good, it surprises you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.34,0:01:53.92,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:56.15,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Other than that... Lemme think...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.15,0:01:59.04,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,You can use it when someone's\N fashion sense is kinda gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.04,0:02:01.71,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Or when you get a bad score on a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.22,0:02:05.12,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But those examples are the \Ntotal opposite of the last two...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.12,0:02:09.32,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I think that word might be a bit \Ntoo complicated for me to master.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.26,0:02:25.95,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I want to ask you something, Ren.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.95,0:02:27.48,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.48,0:02:30.47,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be getting my pay\Nfrom my part-time job soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.47,0:02:32.42,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, payday, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.69,0:02:37.16,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to use that money to repay\N the Saionji family for their hospitality
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.16,0:02:39.68,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,by taking you all out for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.94,0:02:42.79,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.79,0:02:47.13,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,You worked hard for that money, \Nso you should spend it on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.13,0:02:50.08,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,No. I decided on it a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.48,0:02:56.44,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to ask you to help me\Nchoose what restaurant to go to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.83,0:03:01.12,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any places your family \Nreally likes and visits a lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.47,0:03:04.91,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, you're such a sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:08.23,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. It's the least I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.23,0:03:10.54,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I bet Mom and Dad will be thrilled, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.97,0:03:13.25,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I really hope they will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.58,0:03:18.59,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's a surprise, though, so try to \Nkeep it a secret until the day itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.55,0:03:27.51,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.4\b1\fscx90\fnGeorgia\fs14\c&H90562E&\pos(300.667,89.333)\frz63.83\frx8\fry326}Fish
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.33,0:03:27.51,Default,Server,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:29.31,Default,Server,0000,0000,0000,,Your plain shirasu-don.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.93,0:03:33.54,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Even better than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.22,0:03:36.18,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,How is it usually eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:38.95,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I recommend adding \Na little bit of soy sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.95,0:03:41.84,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Try it with some rice. It's really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.60,0:03:45.74,Default,Ren/Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Time to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:48.60,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Close your eyes and... {\fnTimes New Roman}go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.40,0:03:57.54,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's surprisingly good.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.54,0:04:00.57,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at it, I never would've \Nimagined it'd taste so good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.57,0:04:02.59,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Right? Pretty "yabai," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.92,0:04:04.44,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Very "yabai."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.44,0:04:07.20,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Ren, what exactly {\i1}is{\i0} "shirasu"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.20,0:04:10.52,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shirasu's just shirasu.\N Little fish, basically.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.52,0:04:14.98,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Are they baby fish? Or full-grown ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.98,0:04:16.98,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, that, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:18.37,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Let me look it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.22,0:04:24.36,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,"Shirasu" is actually a generic term for \Njuvenile whitefish with no body pigment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:29.01,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,That mostly means sardines, \Nbut also includes pacific herring and eel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:30.60,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.60,0:04:31.64,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,Please enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:33.30,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.30,0:04:35.10,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.10,0:04:36.93,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,That was pretty educational.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.82,0:04:43.51,Italics,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it! That's MFG's\N super rookie, Katagiri Kanata!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.51,0:04:47.51,Italics,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,And he's eating at my place! This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.22,0:04:53.07,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.07,0:04:54.69,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.69,0:04:57.77,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,We'd love to see you here again. And...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.25,0:05:01.03,Default,Owner,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck in the Ashinoko GT.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.93,0:05:06.03,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,So he knew who you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.03,0:05:09.11,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That's never happened before.\N I'm a bit shaken up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:10.99,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.99,0:05:14.96,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,There's 30 million people around\N the world who know you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:19.32,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you should wear sunglasses to hide\N your face like celebrities do overseas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:21.91,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,That wouldn't be very cool.
