Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:07:02.97,Top,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,First and second set \Nnew course records, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.97,0:07:08.16,Default,Yamashita,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredible. And they both beat \Nthe old record by quite some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.16,0:07:12.49,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,What about the unofficial \N"phantom" course record?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:17.54,Default,Yamashita,0000,0000,0000,,Comparing with that lap time,\N they still slightly improved on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.96,0:07:18.96,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.33,0:07:26.40,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,So someone managed to beat Keisuke's\Nall-out "super lap" in our fourth season, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.44,0:07:30.80,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, what's the \Nweather forecast for race day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.80,0:07:34.76,Default,Yamashita,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a pretty high chance of rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.24,0:07:40.49,Default,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good grief. Racing in the rain is \Nalways a mess. We'd better be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.49,0:07:41.35,Default,Yamashita,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.47,0:07:43.99,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:50.44,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,The downhill ace of Project D was a pro\N at dealing with wet conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.41,0:08:00.69,Italics,Joyu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we'll get to see if the same\N is true of his apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.76,0:08:09.88,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ugh, racing in the rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.88,0:08:13.00,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Front-engine, rear-wheel-drive\N cars and rain don't mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.00,0:08:18.03,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna be hugely handicapped up \Nagainst the 4x4s and mid-engine cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.49,0:08:22.01,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The new suspension looked \Nreally promising in qualifying, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.01,0:08:23.94,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:27.70,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that reminds me. \NI'd better give Okuyama-san a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:31.73,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Best to get some advice on \Nthe best setup for rainy conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:41.77,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what'll happen if it rains tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:45.91,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Will I have to do the mini-concert and\N the leaderboard updates while soaked?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:48.70,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,This sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:56.57,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Good afternoon to the 30.12 million\N MFG fans all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.57,0:08:58.95,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I am Tanaka Yoji, your commentator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:03.83,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The June rains are gracefully \Nrippling the surface of Ashinoko Lake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.43,0:09:10.82,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It seems MFG's second round, the Ashinoko GT,\N will be a rain-soaked battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.93,0:09:18.07,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,On guest commentary today, we have \NIkeda Ryuji, the chairman of Zero Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:19.23,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.55,0:09:23.59,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,As well as serving as a city councilor\N for his hometown of Odawara,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.59,0:09:30.70,Default,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,he actively works with youths to improve \Ntheir health and wellbeing through motorsport.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.13,0:09:33.57,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,You can also often \Nfind him clad in vestments,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.57,0:09:36.60,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,serving as head priest in\Nhis family's Buddhist temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.60,0:09:40.02,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,A hat-trick of professions for \Nthis modern-day Renaissance man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.72,0:09:43.30,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Ikeda-san, thank you for joining us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.30,0:09:45.89,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.13,0:09:49.87,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. The dampers are all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.87,0:09:54.44,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't raining further down \Nthe mountain, but it is up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.90,0:10:01.66,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,That's Hakone for you. The weather's always \Ndifferent between the peaks and the base.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:08.24,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You amuse me, Ogata-san. \NWhy do you look so worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:10.28,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.82,0:10:15.09,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,This is about as serious as it gets.\NThe stress is turning my stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.43,0:10:19.51,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Racing on public roads \Nin the wet is madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.96,0:10:22.80,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I'd honestly rather they \Njust cancel the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.21,0:10:27.71,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I get the feeling pretty much \Neveryone involved feels the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:31.74,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,And considering you're in \Na front-engine, rear-wheel-drive car,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:35.73,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,it's gonna be especially \Nsquirrelly on the wet roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.99,0:10:38.66,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata-san, the rain plays fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.57,0:10:44.12,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It falls the same on all 15 cars. \NI don't see it as a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:48.66,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, rain is often a help to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.58,0:10:59.42,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The Angels wrap up their rain-soaked \Nperformance and rush to the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.28,0:11:04.93,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of them singing while soaked\Nsure left a different impression than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.67,0:11:11.17,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I get the feeling fans of the Angels will \Npreserve the video of that one for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.17,0:11:14.15,Default,Kyoko,0000,0000,0000,,I get workers' comp \Nif I get sick from this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.37,0:11:19.07,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and it looks like the \Ndrivers' meeting has concluded,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:22.53,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,and they're all making \Ntheir way to their vehicles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:24.83,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Aiba-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.73,Default,Aiba,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. You, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.98,0:11:34.75,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Ogata here. Can you hear me okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:35.84,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Loud and clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.84,0:11:40.47,Italics,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I left a dry towel on the passenger's seat. \NMake sure to wipe your soles.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.70,0:11:44.95,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,If they're wet, it'll change \Nthe feel of the pedals. Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:45.83,Italics,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnTimes New Roman}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.25,0:11:49.77,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,It's now just five minutes \Nuntil the scheduled start time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.17,0:11:51.64,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a question, Ikeda-san:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:56.44,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,What does a driver have to \Nkeep in mind going into a wet race?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.44,0:11:59.65,Default,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,In a word, they need patience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.08,0:12:05.00,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,In the wet, the way the tires react on public\N roads can change from moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.00,0:12:10.22,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,so you need to constantly evaluate your grip\N while grappling with the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.63,0:12:15.05,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Not only is your visibility limited \Nby the spray from the cars in front,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:19.13,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,you're also in a persistent\N tug of war with your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.55,0:12:22.09,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,And as the difficulties mount up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:26.29,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,it becomes a question of maintaining \Na calm, rational state of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.29,0:12:31.02,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Getting overly aggressive in a race \Nlike this won't yield results.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.36,0:12:35.64,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It sounds like this race will \Nprove to be a real mental challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:37.31,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:41.88,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,These 15 drivers in their cockpits \N waiting for the signal to go
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:47.57,Top Italics,Ikeda,0000,0000,0000,,will face a level of pressure\Nthat's incomparable to a normal race.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.74,0:12:50.97,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The Angels are all lined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.83,0:12:55.71,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,One minute to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.34,0:13:03.54,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,The 12 car in pole position is being \Nguided slowly out of the gate by a drone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.02,0:13:08.82,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Then comes Sawatari in the 4, \NIshigami in the 1 car, and Akaba in the 2 car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.82,0:13:13.89,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Maezono's next in Car 13, followed by \NOishi in the 3 car, then Taylor in the 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:19.65,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,After that, it's Sakamoto in the 5, \NOtani in the 7 car, and Katagiri in the 86.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:26.55,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.99,0:13:29.90,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,All I can really do is pray for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.01,0:13:33.83,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.52,0:13:42.05,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,When Kanata's in serious mode, \Nhe's so cool, time seems to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.75,0:13:44.96,Italics,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,He never looks like that at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.82,0:13:50.51,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,Bringing up the rear, \Nthe 23 passes through the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:53.47,Top Italics,Commentator,0000,0000,0000,,And the drones all signal \Nfor the race to begin!
